    body: "St. Martha of Bethany was a close friend of Jesus who, along with her sister Mary and brother Lazarus, hosted him in their home. In Luke 10, she is gently corrected by Jesus for being anxious about serving while Mary sat at his feet. But in John 11, Martha delivers one of the most powerful professions of faith in the Gospels: when Jesus tells her that Lazarus will rise, she responds, 'I believe that you are the Christ, the Son of the living God.' She is the patron saint of cooks and homemakers.",
    example: "When Jesus arrived after Lazarus's death, Martha ran to meet him while Mary stayed home grieving. Her forthright conversation with Jesus — 'Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died' — shows a faith bold enough to question yet humble enough to trust.",
